<section class="hero">

<h1>
Gen<span>omics</span>
</h1>

<p>
Genomics investigates the complete set of genetic information encoded within DNA. Through sequencing, variant discovery, computational biology, and systems-level analysis, genomics enables precision medicine, disease discovery, and biological understanding across individuals and populations.
</p>

<div class="hero-image">
  <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
    <source src="/genomics-encoded biological information.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
</div>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
What is <span>Genomics?</span>
</h2>

<div class="infographic">

  <img
    src="/2_Genomics.png"
    alt="Genomics overview infographic"
  >

</div>

<p>
Genomics is the study of genomes, the complete DNA content of an organism. It examines genes, regulatory regions, genetic variation, genome structure, and how inherited or acquired changes influence biological function and disease.
</p>

<p>
Modern genomics combines sequencing technologies, computational analysis, population-scale datasets, and biological interpretation to understand health, disease, evolution, and precision medicine.
</p>

</section>

